narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you are interested in the field you have to take it ! Raul is awesome always super friendly and reachable and the discussion was always just at a very high level. Even if you are not into the whole East Asian thing great class to see a different perspective from the same old problems..

This course was a much-needed addition to the almost exclusively Western, and generally very traditional and conservative offerings of the Yale Philosophy curriculum. I would recommend this course to junior and senior philosophy students or anyone who's had a solid introduction to metaphysics and is interested in paraconsistent logics or learning more about Eastern schools of thought from a rigorously metaphysical and logical perspective. The emphasis was on metaphysics more than logic.
